Est√©e Lauder President John Demsey and MAC AIDS Fund Director Nancy Mahon Talk Viva Glam, Nicki Minaj, and Ricky Martin | Vanity FairVanity FairSign InEst√©e Lauder President John Demsey and MAC AIDS Fund Director Nancy Mahon Talk Viva Glam, Nicki Minaj, and Ricky Martinby Evan MulvihillFebruary 21, 2012 6:15 pmEmailFacebookTwitterNicki Minaj and Ricky Martin, faces of MAC's Viva Glam, perform at the Viva Glam launch party.Each year, MAC Cosmetics picks a big-name celebrity to feature on a trademark product for their Viva Glam campaign. Last year, Lady Gaga partnered with the brand to produce Viva Glam Gaga lipstick, which had a sort of taupe-meets-crimson sheen to it; this year, they‚Äôve chosen Nicki Minaj for a bright bubblegum-pink lipstick and Ricky Martin for a colorless unisex lip conditioner. While many corporations wrangle endorsements from famous people at high prices and then hawk the products for higher profits, MAC gives 100 percent of all proceeds from their Viva Glam products to the MAC AIDS Fund.After a whirlwind media tour, with appearances on Good Morning Americaand Live! with Kellyearlier in the day, Nicki and Ricky relaxed at New York City's Stage 37 last week for their much-hyped Viva Glam launch party. Before the bash, we caught two of MAC‚Äôs top execs and chatted them up about the famous duo: Nicki and Ricky‚Äôs rhyming synergy, how they make money off the products, and whether Obama is wearing makeup on-camera.Here‚Äôs what John Demsey, group president of the __Est√©e Lauder Companies,__and Nancy Mahon, global executive director of the MAC AIDS Fund, had to say.Nicki Minaj with John Demsey, group president of the Est√©e Lauder Companies.
How did you choose Nicki and Ricky as the new faces of the Viva Glam campaign?John Demsey: Both of them have huge, diverse platforms in terms of their fan base and audience. In Nicki‚Äôs case, she‚Äôs become one of the leading voices for young people and really has captured the imagination of the day. We also believe she can sell the lipstick. Ricky has been a pop star since he was a young child. He himself is on a trajectory to taking his career to greater heights. It‚Äôs the first time that MAC Cosmetics has ever done a unisex product that can be used by men and women with no shades associated with it. The two are a surprising, fun combination of pop-culture personality, muscle, and fund-raising ability.Nancy Mahon: I‚Äôd just like to add that AIDS is the leading killer of black women in America and abroad. That‚Äôs something Nicki really took to heart. And Nicki‚Äôs uncle died of AIDS himself.You guys give away 100 percent of the proceeds from Nicki‚Äôs lipstick and Ricky‚Äôs lip conditioner, each costing $14.50, to the MAC____AIDS____Fund. Clearly, it‚Äôs a great cause, but how can you make any money off of it?
John: We‚Äôve been doing this for 20 years‚Äîfirst, with RuPaul, and last year, with Lady Gaga. We‚Äôve found that this cause in particular resonates with the staff that works for the brand, as well as the customers around the world who are attracted to our brand. Whenever our Viva Glam business is at an all-time high, so is our overall business. For us, this is not only good work‚Äîit‚Äôs good business.__Nancy:__We as a company give more money to AIDS than any other company in the world. Last year, we raised $38 million and gave that all away. We would be happy for more company, so we not only encourage customers to make a difference but also other companies. It‚Äôs a wonderful testament that you can do good in the world and do good business.In terms of selling the lip conditioner to men, do you think they‚Äôll really buy it?John: A little-known fact is that there probably isn‚Äôt a performance artist, model, film star, newscaster, or journalist‚Äîmale or female‚Äîin the world that doesn‚Äôt have some sort of experience with using a MAC product from time to time. It always amazes me how many men‚Äîpoliticians, professional athletes‚Äîin the era of high-definition television wear makeup as part of projecting their total image.D.J. Benny Benassi performs at the Viva Glam launch party.
__Are you going to name any names here?John:__There‚Äôs hardly a person I can think of that has not used our products.__Obama?John:__ I don‚Äôt know if he has. I know that Michelle has.__How about Brian WIliams?John:__ Everybody does! We‚Äôve come a long way since the Nixon-Kennedy debates, in 1960.__I saw a promo ad that said one lipstick can buy 254 male condoms or 24
female condoms. In terms of where the money will go, do you focus on
prevention, research, or medicine for those who already have the
disease?Nancy__: We certainly do fund condoms‚Äîwe fund a
large range of services‚Äîbut the bulk of what we do is fund food and
housing for people living with AIDS. The bottom line is if you can‚Äôt eat and you don‚Äôt have a roof over your head, you can‚Äôt practice prevention or get better.Ricky Martin flashes a peace sign on his way into the party.
__The Nicki lipstick is bubblegum-pink. Do you think girls will want to go for this really bold color?John:__I‚Äôm
sure of it, because we had a little experiment. When Nicki came to us
before she launched her first album, Pink Friday, she was big fan of a
pink shade of our lipstick, and we actually created a variant of the
shade for her album launch, which we put online only. We thought we
would sell 2,500 pieces over four Fridays last November. We sold 40,000.
If you watched the Grammys, she wore the Viva Glam lipstick during her
performance.__What did you think of that performance? It was
very Catholic-imagery inspired and somewhat blasphemous. Could that turn
off some people?John:__It could. I think she definitely made a statement and got people‚Äôs attention, and that‚Äôs what MAC‚Äôs all about.__Ricky has around 4 or 5 million fans on Twitter, while Nicki has 9 million. Is she the more famous spokesperson of the two?John:__
Ricky has a very surprisingly big fan base in Asia and in the
international markets. He really hasn‚Äôt been focusing on the American
Twitter-using market for quite some time. I don‚Äôt know if you saw his
performance on Glee two weeks ago, or the news that he‚Äôs going to be in
Evita on Broadway, but this campaign coincides with the re-introduction
of Ricky Martin to mainstream America.__Ricky‚Äôs not the first openly gay person you guys have used, either.John:__ We‚Äôve used RuPaul, k.d. lang, and Elton John, so we‚Äôve had everybody from all walks of life associated with the brand.Nancy:
John, I didn‚Äôt get to tell you this, but this morning Nicki told me,
‚ÄúBoy, you guys are really good at this. I really like working with
Ricky.‚Äù So they have very nice chemistry.__And it rhymes!John:__We
didn‚Äôt know it was going to happen this way, but it‚Äôs lining up to be a
very Ricky-and-Nicki moment. And MAC is at the center of it.Full ScreenPhotos:1/12Est√©e Lauder President John Demsey and MAC AIDS Fund Director Nancy Mahon Talk Viva Glam, Nicki Minaj, and Ricky MartinMAC Viva Glam launch party at Stage 37 in N.Y.C.John Demsey, group president of Est√©e Lauder Companies, and Ricky Martin, who is the face of MAC's new colorless lip conditioner.D.J. Benny Benassi performs for the crowd.Nicki Minaj shows off her bubblegum-pink MAC Viva Glam lipstick shade.Alina ChoDerek BlasbergMAC AIDS fund director Nancy Mahon.PreviousNextMAC Viva Glam launch party at Stage 37 in N.Y.C.John Demsey, group president of Est√©e Lauder Companies, and Ricky Martin, who is the face of MAC's new colorless lip conditioner.D.J. Benny Benassi performs for the crowd.Nicki Minaj shows off her bubblegum-pink MAC Viva Glam lipstick shade.Coco RochaAnna Shilling, Christian Siriano and Brad WalshTinsley MortimerBrad GoreskiKelly OsbourneAlina ChoDerek BlasbergMAC AIDS fund director Nancy Mahon.ShareEmailFacebookTwitterYOU MIGHT LIKEThe Year of Titanic Cast Reunions Has ArrivedVanity FairThe One Thing Prince William and Kate Middleton Ban from Their HomeVanity FairQueen Elizabeth‚Äôs Rainbow Closet of CoatsVanity FairSee Angelina Jolie‚Äôs Transformation from Young Starlet to Global HumanitarianVanity FairPrince George and Princess Charlotte‚Äôs Most Adorable Moments on the 2017 Poland/Germany TourVanity FairMelania Trump Will Soon Hang Out with Prince Harry for a WeekVanity FairAround the WebPowered by ZergnetRELATEDSEEKThe Year of Titanic Cast Reunions Has ArrivedBY HILARY WEAVERThe One Thing Prince William and Kate Middleton Ban from Their HomeBY JOSH DUBOFFSEEK


